Saw that vid a while back, but it's still awesome. Thanks for posting it.

That's crazy but oddly familiar. Back when I lived and worked in Manila, each morning on the way to work there'd be 2-3 guys with high powered rifles trained onto the surface of this disgustingly muddy river. Apparantly every once in a while a fish would surface (usually catfish) and they'd blast 'em  . Others waiting on the rivers edge would scoop them up with nets.  Living in any 3rd world country sure gives one a better appreciation of Canada  .
It's just the adult version of the one I've seen advertised on the Fishin Canada show.  :lol:
Never mind the launcher - I imagine a missile refill costs a few more bucks than a Rapala!  Next time I lose one to a snag I won't feel so bad!
I think it depends on what size Rapala. What's he using...J?
